# Rule: .agents/memory/README.md

Documents the procedure for adding memory entries. The actual procedure
lives in `.agents/skills/maintaining-agents-dir/SKILL.md`; this README is
the index of the three subdirectories and the frontmatter shape.

## Template

```markdown
# `.agents/memory/` — the agent's shared knowledge

> **What this is.** A flat store of facts, retros, and lessons…

## Layout

```
.agents/memory/
├── README.md (this file)
├── facts/    — non-obvious facts we learned
├── retros/   — retrospectives on mistakes
├── lessons/  — behaviour-changing lessons
└── index.tsv — generated; never edit by hand
```

## Frontmatter shape

```yaml
---
id: <kebab-case>
type: fact | retro | lesson
tags: [kebab, kebab]
created: YYYY-MM-DD
summary: <one sentence>
---
```

- `id` — kebab-case, unique within `type`. Example: `pidChain-beats-sessionId`.
- `type` — `fact`, `retro`, or `lesson`. Each lives in its own subdir.
- `tags` — array of kebab tokens. Reuse existing tags where possible; check
  the index (`bun run memory:reindex`) first.
- `summary` — single sentence; the agent should be able to make a decision
  from this line alone.

## Reindex

`bun run memory:reindex` walks this folder, parses frontmatter, and
writes `index.tsv`. Re-run after every add.
```
